gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Celtics 101, Kings 100
gameRecap.excerpt: The Kings finished the game on a 21-3 run in the final 5:49 of the game, but the Celtics held on to win the game, 101-100. Payton Pritchard led Boston with 21 points and five 3PM as Kristaps Porzingis added 20 points and 11 rebounds. De’Aaron Fox totaled 40 points, seven 3PM and four rebounds as Domantas Sabonis totaled 16 points, 16 rebounds, and six assists. Boston has now won four in a row as they move to 61-16 while the Kings move to 44-33 and now share the same record with the nine-seed Lakers.
